/*!
    \page index.html

    \title Qt Quick Components

    \image common/component-splash.png

    Qt Quick Components provides a set of QML components for building user 
    interfaces. The components allow the interface to accept user input and 
    provide feedback indicators.
    
    This documentation covers Qt Quick Components for Symbian.
    The \l {http://harmattan-dev.nokia.com/docs/library/html/qt-components/qt-components.html?tab=0#getting-started-with-the-components}
    {Qt Quick Components for MeeGo}
    documentation covers MeeGo-specific Qt Quick Components.
    
    Regarding Qt Quick and Qt Quick Components, note the following:
    \list
        \o  \l {http://doc.qt.nokia.com/4.7-snapshot/qml-intro.html}
        {Qt Quick} is part of Qt from Qt 4.7 onwards, whereas Qt Quick 
        Components is an add-on module to Qt Quick
        \o In QML, Qt Quick has its own \c import statement, for example \c 
        {import QtQuick 1.0}, whereas Qt Quick Components has three \c import 
        statements listed in the code snippet below.
    \endlist

    Qt Quick Components consists of three component sets: one for the Symbian 
    platform, one for the MeeGo platform, and the \e{Extras} set that is common for 
    Symbian and MeeGo platforms. Each set has a different \c import statement as 
    follows:

    \code
    import com.nokia.symbian 1.1    // Symbian components
    import com.nokia.meego 1.0      // MeeGo components
    import com.nokia.extras 1.0     // Extras
    \endcode

